{"id":572928957,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"2 years, 2 months","timestamp":1634520236,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"68 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/572928957/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"14.3 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        # first, convert both linked lists to ints\n        result = ListNode()\n        result_it = result\n        while True:\n            carry = 0\n            if l1 != None:\n                result_it.val += l1.val\n                l1 = l1.next\n            if l2 != None:\n                result_it.val += l2.val\n                l2 = l2.next\n\n            if result_it.val > 9:\n                carry = 1\n                result_it.val %= 10\n\n            if l1 == None and l2 == None and carry == 0: # nothing more to add\n                break\n            else:\n                result_it.next = ListNode(carry)\n                result_it = result_it.next\n\n        return result","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
